{"ts":"2026-06-26T18:15:56.927Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"a3vucbik","input":{"summary":"Completed the implementation of 'local save copy and share-ready Blueprint report actions' for the Sovereign Enterprise AI Blueprint Generator. \n\nSteps taken and features implemented:\n1. Re-declared 'initialData' at the module scope level to prevent unnecessary React hook re-evaluations, completely resolving exhaustive-deps warnings.\n2. Added state hooks to keep track of local vault history, loaded states, sliding drawer visibility, and various micro-interaction successes (copied, saved, shared).\n3. Developed base64 serialization ('handleShareLink') to compress and encode the user's configuration parameter inside the URL query string ('?share=...'), enabling instant configuration recovery for other users with zero server telemetry.\n4. Implemented a URL-detection hook in 'useEffect' that automatically decodes shared configurations and compiles the matching scoreboards, solutions, and roadmap timeline on page load. Used HTML5 History API to replace the address bar with a clean path after decoding to preserve pristine UX.\n5. Built 'handleSaveLocally' and 'handleDeleteSavedItem' which store up to 10 generated blueprints in the browser's localStorage for instant local retrieval, maintaining the air-gapped Zero-Telemetry security guarantee.\n6. Integrated a beautiful Action Toolbar in 'renderResult' containing:\n   - Secure Local Indicator: Styled with a pulsed green LED highlighting zero data transmission.\n   - Copy Summary Action: Extracts a beautifully organized text summary to the clipboard.\n   - Save Locally Action: Caches the report to the local browser Vault.\n   - Share Report Action: Generates and copies the secure base64 share link.\n   - Print/PDF Action: Triggers native print styles to export standard PDF reports.\n7. Added a top-header 'Saved Vault' button with a badge counting active saved blueprints.\n8. Implemented a fully responsive right-sliding History Drawer to list, load, and delete cached entries.\n\nValidation Results:\n- Passed 'npm run lint' with 0 errors and 0 warnings.\n- The UI is mobile-friendly, accessible, and fully matches the premium 2026 GFF AI enterprise theme.","verified":true}}}
